post_text: Students are returning to the piano lab this year. Many changes have been made to make the room safe for students to return. Details are available in the Fall 2020 edition of Music Notes (under the ‚ÄúNews‚Äù link at jgmusic.weebly.com). Remote learners can take piano lessons as well. Access to a piano or keyboard is needed. (Keyboards are available for a reasonable price through B & J Music and other reputable music stores. Suggested models can be found in the Keyboard Purchase Options file at the above site.) Remote students can participate via live stream lessons with their class during regular school hours or via recorded video lessons if they are not able to attend during regular school hours. More information on signing up for remote lessons will be available soon.

post_text:
Chromebooks distribution for WHS and WJHS went great today. If you were unable to pick up your Chromebook please call ahead and make arrangements to pick up your Chromebook for ALL WHS and WJHS learners (in-person and remote) on Friday August 21st if possible.

Instructions for how to start up your Chromebook can be found here:

https://core-docs.s3.amazonaws.com/documents/asset/uploaded_file/874073/2020_8-20_Chromebook_How_to_Guide.pdf

Information on how to access online curriculum will come shortly (teachers are almost done loading their materials). Information on Giacoma device distribution is also coming shortly as well. No Giacoma remote learning student will be penalized or delayed if the devices that have shipped are unable to be delivered by Monday August 24. We anticipate it shortly and will continue to be flexible and adapt in the meantime. Thank you for your patience.

Find a Way - Together, we can do this!

post_text:
Any 9-12 WHS student who is interested in playing Golf this fall, there will be a player/parent informational meeting this Sunday August 9 at 3:00pm at the WHS parking lot next to the softball field. In case of severe weather, I ask that everyone bring a mask in case we must move inside where a mask is mandatory to enter the school.

The first official practice will be Monday August 10, at 11:30am at Harrison Park. More information about season will be handed out and discussed at meeting.

If you have not turned in a physical form already, please bring it with you Sunday to the meeting as you will not be able to practice without one.

Thank you!
Coach Simpson

post_text:
The IESA, which governs elementary and junior high sports, has made a decision to cancel junior high baseball and softball for this fall. At this time all junior sports activities for the district will be suspended until more decisions are made about junior high and elementary sports potentially occurring later in the school year. This temporary suspension will apply to summer activities for junior and elementary students at Westviille, but will NOT impact high school activities at this point. Incoming freshmen may continue to participate in scheduled high school activities.

We understand the disappointment this will create for our students and families and will continue to seek safe solutions in the future.

Thank you for your support of Westville Schools.

post_text:
Westville School District School Community,

Locker clear out begins tonight at WHS for Sophomores. At Giacoma classroom material pick-up starts for Kindergarten, Preschool, and Early Childhood at the east entrance and Third Grade on the northwest circle drive. The Seventh Grade will have materials pick-up at WJHS. Check the district website at www.gowestville.org for a detailed schedule.

Some important things to remember -

1) WHS students must bring a mask and wear it when on campus during locker clear out. Gloves will be provided by the school district.

2) While we all miss our students, the locker clear out process has been designed to run quickly and smoothly to minimize exposure.

3) Social distancing will be maintained at all times during locker clear out ‚Äì both inside and outside the building. Law enforcement will be assisting in supervision to ensure safe procedures.



Thank you

post_text:
Good afternoon this is a message from Westville School District,

In light of recent events in East Central Illinois and out of an abundance of caution regarding COVID-19, Westville School District will be CANCELING STUDENT ATTENDANCE for tomorrow Monday March 16.

Teachers will report for a Teachers Institute Day from 8AM ‚Äì 1PM.

Students and/or families that may need access to resources, medicine, and/or personal effects may contact the administrative office at each school tomorrow to make arrangements to pick those materials up before 1pm.

The state mandated school closure will begin Tuesday March 17 and last until March 30th.

An email will be sent to all district staff Sunday March 15 concerning planning during tomorrow‚Äôs Teachers Institute Day.

More information will be made available as this situation continues to develop.

post_text:
To further safeguard our communities from the spread of the coronavirus, Governor JB Pritzker has declared mandatory school closures for all schools, both public and private, serving Illinois pre-kindergarten through 12th grade students.

This mandatory closure takes effect Tuesday, March 17. Currently, we anticipate the closure to last through March 30.

The Westville School District administrative team is implementing a contingency plan in response to the Governor's decision and more information will be shared this evening on our district website, social media page, and through parent email.
